arguments: {"context": {"sessionId": "session_1731713900000_r7s8t9u0v", "workspaceId": "ws_1731713900000_w1x2y3z4a", "sessionDescription": "Creating testing strategy", "sessionMemory": "QA documentation", "toolContext": "Strategy documentation", "primaryGoal": "Document testing approach", "subgoal": "Create strategy doc"}, "filePath": "/docs/testing/strategy.md", "content": "# Testing Strategy

## Overview

Our testing strategy ensures code quality through multiple layers of automated and manual testing.

## Test Pyramid

```
        /\
       /E2E\      <- Few (5%)
      /------\
     /  API   \    <- Some (15%)
    /----------\
   /Integration \  <- More (30%)
  /--------------\
 /     Unit       \ <- Most (50%)
/------------------\
```

## Test Types

### 1. Unit Tests (50% of tests)

**Purpose**: Test individual functions and components in isolation

**Coverage Target**: 80% minimum

**Tools**: Jest, React Testing Library

**Example**:
```typescript
describe('calculateTotal', () => {
  it('should sum array of numbers', () => {
    expect(calculateTotal([1, 2, 3])).toBe(6);
  });

  it('should return 0 for empty array', () => {
    expect(calculateTotal([])).toBe(0);
  });

  it('should handle negative numbers', () => {
    expect(calculateTotal([-1, 2, -3])).toBe(-2);
  });
});
```

**Best Practices**:
- Test one thing per test
- Use descriptive test names
- Follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)
- Mock external dependencies
- Keep tests fast (<1ms per test)

### 2. Integration Tests (30% of tests)

**Purpose**: Test interactions between modules

**Coverage**: Critical user flows

**Tools**: Jest, Supertest

**Example**:
```typescript
describe('User Registration Flow', () => {
  it('should create user and send welcome email', async () => {
    // Arrange
    const userData = { email: 'test@example.com', password: 'Pass123!' };

    // Act
    const response = await request(app)
      .post('/api/users/register')
      .send(userData);

    // Assert
    expect(response.status).toBe(201);
    expect(response.body.user.email).toBe(userData.email);

    // Verify email sent
    const emails = await getTestEmails();
    expect(emails).toContainEqual(
      expect.objectContaining({
        to: userData.email,
        subject: 'Welcome'
      })
    );
  });
});
```

### 3. API Tests (15% of tests)

**Purpose**: Test API endpoints end-to-end

**Coverage**: All API endpoints

**Tools**: Supertest, Jest

**Example**:
```typescript
describe('GET /api/users/:id', () => {
  it('should return user by id', async () => {
    const response = await request(app)
      .get('/api/users/123')
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);

    expect(response.status).toBe(200);
    expect(response.body).toMatchObject({
      id: '123',
      email: expect.any(String)
    });
  });

  it('should return 404 for non-existent user', async () => {
    const response = await request(app)
      .get('/api/users/999')
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);

    expect(response.status).toBe(404);
  });
});
```

### 4. E2E Tests (5% of tests)

**Purpose**: Test critical user journeys in real browser

**Coverage**: Happy paths and critical flows

**Tools**: Playwright, Cypress

**Example**:
```typescript
test('user can complete checkout', async ({ page }) => {
  // Login
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.fill('[name=email]', 'user@example.com');
  await page.fill('[name=password]', 'password');
  await page.click('button[type=submit]');

  // Add to cart
  await page.goto('/products/123');
  await page.click('button:has-text("Add to Cart")');

  // Checkout
  await page.goto('/cart');
  await page.click('button:has-text("Checkout")');

  // Fill payment
  await page.fill('[name=cardNumber]', '4242424242424242');
  await page.fill('[name=expiry]', '12/25');
  await page.fill('[name=cvc]', '123');

  // Submit
  await page.click('button:has-text("Pay Now")');

  // Verify
  await expect(page.locator('text=Order Confirmed')).toBeVisible();
});
```

## Test Organization

### File Structure

```
tests/
├── unit/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── services/
│   └── components/
├── integration/
│   ├── api/
│   └── flows/
├── e2e/
│   ├── user-flows/
│   └── admin-flows/
├── fixtures/
│   ├── users.json
│   └── products.json
└── helpers/
    ├── setup.ts
    └── teardown.ts
```

### Naming Conventions

- Unit tests: `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts`
- Integration tests: `*.integration.test.ts`
- E2E tests: `*.e2e.test.ts`

## CI/CD Integration

### Pre-commit
```bash
npm run test:changed  # Test only changed files
npm run lint
```

### PR Pipeline
```yaml
steps:
  - name: Unit Tests
    run: npm run test:unit

  - name: Integration Tests
    run: npm run test:integration

  - name: Coverage Check
    run: npm run test:coverage
    # Fail if coverage < 80%
```

### Main Branch
```yaml
steps:
  - name: All Tests
    run: npm test

  - name: E2E Tests
    run: npm run test:e2e

  - name: Deploy
    if: success()
    run: npm run deploy
```

## Coverage Requirements

- **Overall**: 80% minimum
- **Critical paths**: 100%
- **New code**: 90% minimum
- **Utilities**: 95% minimum

## Test Data Management

### Fixtures

Use fixtures for consistent test data:

```typescript
// fixtures/users.ts
export const testUsers = {
  admin: {
    email: 'admin@example.com',
    role: 'admin'
  },
  regular: {
    email: 'user@example.com',
    role: 'user'
  }
};
```

### Factories

Use factories for dynamic test data:

```typescript
// factories/userFactory.ts
export const createUser = (overrides = {}) => ({
  id: faker.datatype.uuid(),
  email: faker.internet.email(),
  name: faker.name.fullName(),
  created: new Date(),
  ...overrides
});
```

## Mocking Strategy

### External Services

Mock all external services in tests:

```typescript
jest.mock('./emailService', () => ({
  sendEmail: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({ sent: true })
}));
```

### Database

Use in-memory database for tests:

```typescript
beforeAll(async () => {
  await connectToTestDB();
});

afterAll(async () => {
  await disconnectFromTestDB();
});
```

## Performance Testing

See [Performance Guidelines](/docs/testing/performance-guidelines.md)

## Manual Testing

### When to Manually Test

- Visual design changes
- Complex user interactions
- Accessibility features
- Browser compatibility
- Mobile responsiveness

### Testing Checklist

- [ ] Test in Chrome, Firefox, Safari
- [ ] Test on mobile devices
- [ ] Test with screen reader
- [ ] Test keyboard navigation
- [ ] Test with slow network

## Continuous Improvement

### Metrics to Track

- Test coverage percentage
- Test execution time
- Flaky test rate
- Bug escape rate
- Time to fix bugs

### Regular Reviews

- Weekly: Review failed tests
- Monthly: Review coverage reports
- Quarterly: Update testing strategy

## Resources

- [Jest Documentation](https://jestjs.io/)
- [Testing Library](https://testing-library.com/)
- [Playwright](https://playwright.dev/)"}

