arguments: {"context": {"sessionId": "session_1731773700000_p9q0r1s2t", "workspaceId": "ws_1731773700000_u3v4w5x6y", "sessionDescription": "Creating webhook guide", "sessionMemory": "Integration documentation", "toolContext": "Guide creation", "primaryGoal": "Document webhooks", "subgoal": "Create webhook guide"}, "filePath": "/docs/integrations/webhooks.md", "content": "# Webhook Integration Guide

## Overview

Webhooks allow you to receive real-time notifications when events occur in our system.

## Setup

### 1. Create Webhook Endpoint

Create an HTTPS endpoint to receive webhook payloads:

```javascript
app.post('/webhooks', async (req, res) => {
  const signature = req.headers['x-webhook-signature'];

  // Verify signature
  const isValid = verifySignature(req.body, signature);
  if (!isValid) {
    return res.status(401).send('Invalid signature');
  }

  const event = req.body;

  // Process event
  await handleEvent(event);

  res.status(200).send('OK');
});
```

### 2. Register Webhook

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.example.com/v3/webhooks \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
    "url": "https://your-domain.com/webhooks",
    "events": ["user.created", "order.completed"],
    "secret": "your_webhook_secret"
  }'
```

## Event Types

### User Events
- `user.created`: New user registered
- `user.updated`: User profile updated
- `user.deleted`: User account deleted

### Order Events
- `order.created`: New order placed
- `order.completed`: Order fulfilled
- `order.cancelled`: Order cancelled

### Payment Events
- `payment.succeeded`: Payment successful
- `payment.failed`: Payment failed

## Payload Format

```json
{
  "id": "evt_1234567890",
  "type": "order.completed",
  "created": "2024-11-16T20:00:00Z",
  "data": {
    "order_id": "ord_abc123",
    "customer_id": "cus_xyz789",
    "total": 99.99
  }
}
```

## Signature Verification

```javascript
const crypto = require('crypto');

function verifySignature(payload, signature) {
  const secret = process.env.WEBHOOK_SECRET;
  const hmac = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret);
  const digest = hmac.update(JSON.stringify(payload)).digest('hex');

  return crypto.timingSafeEqual(
    Buffer.from(signature),
    Buffer.from(digest)
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Respond Quickly

```javascript
app.post('/webhooks', async (req, res) => {
  // Acknowledge immediately
  res.status(200).send('OK');

  // Process asynchronously
  processWebhookAsync(req.body);
});
```

### 2. Handle Retries

- Implement idempotency using event IDs
- Store processed event IDs to prevent duplicates

```javascript
const processedEvents = new Set();

if (processedEvents.has(event.id)) {
  return; // Already processed
}

await handleEvent(event);
processedEvents.add(event.id);
```

### 3. Monitor Failures

- Log all webhook processing errors
- Set up alerts for high failure rates
- We retry failed webhooks 3 times with exponential backoff

### 4. Security

- Always verify webhook signatures
- Use HTTPS endpoints only
- Whitelist our webhook IPs (provided in dashboard)

## Testing

```bash
# Trigger test webhook
curl -X POST https://api.example.com/v3/webhooks/test \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \
  -d '{"webhook_id": "wh_123", "event_type": "user.created"}'
```"}

